data.description: This move-in-ready 4 bed, 3 FULL bath home includes a few "unique to Austin" features! For example: the downstairs bathroom vanity is made from reclaimed wood from the first bar ever built on Rainey Street; Lustre Pearl! The tile located on the front of the shower, as well as the back patio you’ll only find in the penthouse at the tippy top of the 4 seasons! When you first enter, you'll notice how the stamped concrete floors downstairs sparkle! They've been stripped, cleaned & re-sealed! The stairs & the entire second floor are luxury vinyl wood plank flooring, except the bathrooms that boast a combination of ceramic, slate and porcelain tile. This home is also equipped with an on demand hot water heater! You can have multiple showers going, the washing machine & the kitchen sink on at the same time, & you will not lose pressure or heat! The hot water heater, fireplace, HVAC, and range are natural gas. The laundry room has the option for electric or gas for the dryer. This home is located withing a "hospital grid" so it did not lose power during the freeze!! The entire home has been freshly painted, inside and out! The back wooden deck leading out to the tropical paradise of a yard has been completely replaced and sealed! The back yard has been well loved over the past 17 years! The back yard is truly a tropical paradise! With a seasonal creek, banana trees, canna lilies, & elephant ears that come back every year providing beautiful foliage, the back yard/ patio is perfect for entertaining! Pride of ownership is very apparent! The back yard also has a 16x20 shed that had been converted to a livable space. It is heated, cooled & has internet. Perfect for a small guest suite, office, or workshop! It was used as an office for years. The home is directly across the street from overflow parking spaces. Home is also equipped with a built-in doghouse under the stairs, a fenced dog run, as well as space under the deck that has been used for dogs, chickens, & dry storage!
